annotationA: GH03305p; NAD binding; phosphoglycerate dehydrogenase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: oxidation-reduction process; Belongs to the D-isomer specific 2-hydroxyacid dehydrogenase family
annotationB: Probable phosphoserine aminotransferase; Catalyzes the reversible conversion of 3- phosphohydroxypyruvate to phosphoserine and of 3-hydroxy-2-oxo-4- phosphonooxybutanoate to phosphohydroxythreonine; Belongs to the class-V pyridoxal-phosphate-dependent aminotransferase family. SerC subfamily
